==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seedsman
<hw>Seeds"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Seedsmen</plw> <pr>(-m⟦eit⟧n)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sower;
one who sows or scatters seed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>seedsman</qex>⟦br⟧
Upon the slime and ooze scatters his grain.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who deals in seeds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seedtime</ent>⟦br⟧
